## AIWG SDLC Framework

This project uses the **AI Writing Guide (AIWG) SDLC framework** with Factory AI droids for comprehensive software development lifecycle management.

### What is AIWG?

AIWG provides:
- **53 specialized droids** covering all SDLC phases (Inception → Elaboration → Construction → Transition → Production)
- **42+ commands** for project management, security, testing, deployment, and traceability
- **100+ templates** for requirements, architecture, testing, security, and deployment artifacts
- **Phase-based workflows** with gate criteria and milestone tracking
- **Multi-agent orchestration** for collaborative artifact generation

### Deployed Droids

**Location:** `.factory/droids/` (53 SDLC droids)

**Key Droids by Category:**

**Intake & Planning:**
- `intake-coordinator` - Generates and validates project intake forms
- `requirements-analyst` - Documents vision, user stories, use cases
- `system-analyst` - Bridges business intent and technical delivery
- `business-process-analyst` - Models business processes and value flows
- `product-strategist` - Shapes product vision and positioning

**Architecture:**
- `architecture-designer` - Creates software architecture documents (SAD)
- `api-designer` - Designs and evolves API contracts
- `architecture-documenter` - Documents architecture artifacts with precision
- `cloud-architect` - Designs multi-cloud infrastructure (AWS/Azure/GCP)

**Security:**
- `security-architect` - Leads threat modeling and security requirements
- `security-gatekeeper` - Applies security gates and generates pass/fail reports
- `security-auditor` - Reviews code for vulnerabilities and OWASP compliance
- `privacy-officer` - Ensures lawful data processing and GDPR compliance

**Testing:**
- `test-engineer` - Creates comprehensive test suites (unit, integration, E2E)
- `test-architect` - Designs holistic test strategies and quality governance
- `test-documenter` - Documents test artifacts with traceability
- `accessibility-specialist` - Ensures WCAG 2.1 AA/AAA compliance

**Operations:**
- `devops-engineer` - Automates CI/CD, infrastructure as code, deployment
- `reliability-engineer` - Establishes SLO/SLI, capacity testing, ORR
- `deployment-manager` - Orchestrates release planning and deployment
- `incident-responder` - Handles production incidents with urgency
- `support-lead` - Prepares customer support readiness and knowledge management
- `environment-engineer` - Tailors process assets, tooling, guidelines

**Documentation:**
- `technical-writer` - Ensures documentation clarity and consistency
- `documentation-synthesizer` - Merges multi-agent feedback into cohesive artifacts
- `documentation-archivist` - Manages drafts, version history, audit trails

**Quality & Performance:**
- `code-reviewer` - Comprehensive code reviews (quality, security, performance)
- `performance-engineer` - Profiles bottlenecks, conducts load testing, optimizes
- `metrics-analyst` - Defines and interprets delivery/product metrics

**Specialized Roles:**
- `debugger` - Systematic debugging for errors and test failures
- `database-optimizer` - Optimizes queries, designs indexes, handles migrations
- `legacy-modernizer` - Refactors legacy code, migrates frameworks
- `api-documenter` - Creates OpenAPI/Swagger specs and SDKs
- `configuration-manager` - Governs version control, baselines, change processes
- `traceability-manager` - Maintains requirements → code → tests → release mapping
- `decision-matrix-expert` - Facilitates data-driven trade-off decisions
- `raci-expert` - Facilitates responsibility assignments (RACI matrix)

[Full droid list: 53 total in `.factory/droids/`]

### Using AIWG Droids

**Direct Invocation:**
```text
"Use requirements-analyst to review this user story"
"Ask security-architect to evaluate authentication design"
"Have test-engineer create test plan for payment flow"
```

**Natural Language Orchestration:**

Factory automatically maps natural language to droids:

```text
"Start security review"        → security-architect + security-gatekeeper + security-auditor
"Create architecture baseline" → architecture-designer + reviewers + synthesizer
"Generate test plan"           → test-architect + test-engineer
"Deploy to production"         → deployment-manager + reliability-engineer
"Run iteration 5"              → Entire iteration workflow
```

**Multi-Agent Workflows:**

Factory handles parallel execution automatically:

**Pattern: Primary Author → Parallel Reviewers → Synthesizer → Archive**

```text
You: "Create comprehensive SAD for microservices platform"

Factory orchestrates:
1. architecture-designer creates draft
2. Parallel review (launched simultaneously):
   - security-architect validates security controls
   - test-architect checks testability  
   - requirements-analyst verifies traceability
   - technical-writer ensures clarity
3. documentation-synthesizer merges all feedback
4. Final SAD saved to .aiwg/architecture/software-architecture-doc.md
```

### Project Artifacts (.aiwg/)

All SDLC artifacts stored in `.aiwg/`:

```
.aiwg/
├── intake/              # Project intake forms
├── requirements/        # User stories, use cases, NFRs
├── architecture/        # SAD, ADRs, diagrams
├── planning/            # Phase and iteration plans
├── risks/               # Risk register and mitigation
├── testing/             # Test strategy, plans, results
├── security/            # Threat models, security reviews
├── quality/             # Code reviews, retrospectives
├── deployment/          # Deployment plans, runbooks
├── team/                # Team profile, agent assignments
├── working/             # Temporary scratch (safe to delete)
└── reports/             # Generated reports and indices
```

### Phase Workflows

**Inception** (4-6 weeks):
- intake-coordinator validates intake forms
- requirements-analyst documents vision and business case
- security-architect performs initial security screening
- **Milestone**: Lifecycle Objective (LO)

**Elaboration** (4-8 weeks):
- architecture-designer creates Software Architecture Document (SAD)
- test-architect defines test strategy
- security-architect performs threat modeling
- **Milestone**: Lifecycle Architecture (LA)

**Construction** (8-16 weeks):
- Iterative feature implementation
- test-engineer validates quality with comprehensive tests
- code-reviewer ensures standards and best practices
- **Milestone**: Initial Operational Capability (IOC)

**Transition** (2-4 weeks):
- deployment-manager orchestrates production release
- reliability-engineer validates operational readiness
- support-lead prepares handover and documentation
- **Milestone**: Product Release (PR)

**Production** (ongoing):
- incident-responder handles production issues
- performance-engineer optimizes system performance
- Continuous monitoring and improvement

### Common Commands

```bash
# Project status
"Where are we?" or "What's next?"

# Phase transitions
"Transition to Elaboration"
"Move to Construction"
"Start Transition phase"

# Reviews and validation
"Run security review"
"Execute test strategy"
"Check compliance for SOC2"
"Validate GDPR compliance"

# Artifact generation
"Create architecture baseline"
"Generate test plan"
"Build risk register"
"Document deployment runbook"

# Iteration workflows
"Run iteration 3"
"Start discovery track for iteration 4"
"Execute delivery track for iteration 3"

# Gate checks
"Check if we're ready to move to Construction"
"Validate Elaboration gate criteria"
"Check IOC gate status"
```

### SDLC Commands

**Location:** `.factory/commands/` (42+ flow commands)

**Phase Transitions:**
- `flow-concept-to-inception` - Execute Inception phase
- `flow-inception-to-elaboration` - Transition to Elaboration
- `flow-elaboration-to-construction` - Transition to Construction
- `flow-construction-to-transition` - Transition to Transition

**Continuous Workflows:**
- `flow-risk-management-cycle` - Ongoing risk tracking
- `flow-requirements-evolution` - Living requirements management
- `flow-architecture-evolution` - Architecture refinement
- `flow-test-strategy-execution` - Execute test strategy
- `flow-security-review-cycle` - Security validation
- `flow-performance-optimization` - Performance baseline and optimization

**Gate Validation:**
- `flow-gate-check <phase>` - Validate phase gate criteria
- `flow-handoff-checklist <from> <to>` - Phase handoff validation
- `project-status` - Current phase, milestone progress, next steps
- `project-health-check` - Overall project health metrics

**Team & Process:**
- `flow-team-onboarding <member> [role]` - Onboard new team member
- `flow-knowledge-transfer <from> <to>` - Knowledge transfer workflow
- `flow-retrospective-cycle <type>` - Retrospective facilitation

**Deployment & Operations:**
- `flow-deploy-to-production` - Production deployment
- `flow-hypercare-monitoring <days>` - Post-launch monitoring
- `flow-incident-response <id> [severity]` - Production incident triage

**Intake Methods** (choose ONE for new projects):
- `intake-wizard` - Generate intake interactively
- `intake-from-codebase` - Analyze existing codebase to generate intake
- `intake-start` - Enhance user-provided intake files

### Configuration

**AIWG Installation:** `~/.local/share/ai-writing-guide`

**Verify Installation:**
```bash
ls ~/.local/share/ai-writing-guide/agentic/code/frameworks/sdlc-complete/

# Available resources:
# - agents/     → SDLC role agents (source)
# - commands/   → Slash commands (source)
# - templates/  → 100+ artifact templates
# - flows/      → Phase workflow documentation
```

**Deployed Resources:**
```bash
ls .factory/droids/     # 53 SDLC droids
ls .factory/commands/   # 42+ flow commands
ls .aiwg/               # SDLC artifacts
```

### Customizing Droids

Edit any droid to adjust behavior:

```bash
code .factory/droids/architecture-designer.md
```

**Customize:**
- `model`: Change to faster/slower model (opus, sonnet, haiku)
- `tools`: Restrict to specific tools (remove Execute for safety)
- System prompt: Adjust behavior, style, focus areas

**Example:**
```yaml
---
name: architecture-designer
description: Creates software architecture documents
model: claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929  # Changed from opus for speed/cost
tools: ["Read", "LS", "Grep", "Glob", "Edit", "Create"]  # Removed Execute
---
```

